description:
Comic Related Roles

William Earle

Hauer played William Earle in the Christopher Nolan-directed reboot of the Batman franchise, Batman Begins. Earle was CEO of Wayne Enterprises in Bruce Wayne's stead following the murders of Thomas and Martha Wayne.

Cardinal Roark

Hauer played Cardinal Roark in Sin City, a film directed by Robert Rodriguez and Frank Miller, based on Miller's popular comic book franchise.

Cardinal Roark held great power over Basin City, power that allowed him to seat his brother as state senator. Believing that a cannibal serial killer by the name of Kevin can communicate with God, Roark helps Kevin in his endeavors, leading him to cross paths with Marv, who kills him in an act of vengeance.
name: Rutger Hauer

deck: English comedian, television and radio presenter, director, writer and actor.
description:
Biography

Joe cornish began his career as one half of the comedy duo Adam and Joe, along with childhood friend Adam Buxton. He continued his work as a presenter and writer after their comedy sketch show The Adam and Joe Show ended in 2001. He directed his first film, Attack the Block, in 2011 and also co-write The Adventures of Tin Tin with Edgar Wright. Cornish and Wright are currently working together again, for the upcoming Marvel release Ant-Man, due for release in 2015.
